{"key":"processedPost-7454606","value":{"id":7454606,"first":7454227,"last":7461079,"when":1190810306,"utime":"09/26/07 03:38 PM","cleanedPost":"Pan cyan mycelium is whispy and light, so is often mistaken for contaminants.  I wouldn't recommend sterilizing manure or straw.  When you get a clean culture, inoculate grains, and then when they fully colonize, spawn them into pasterurized horse manure.  Pans do best with a thin substrate, about 1 1/2\" thick.  Use a thin casing layer too, 1/4\" thick.<br />RR"}}